Interview Question: "What is the difference between Vulnerability Assessment and Penetration Testing?"

"Sir, anyone can tell you that VA identifies, PT exploits.
But from a Risk Management perspective, Penetration Testing is fundamentally a test of our Detective and Corrective Controls, not just our Preventive ones. Vulnerability Assessment finds missing patches (Preventive controls). My Penetration Test exploits them to see if the SOC detects the attack (Detective) and if the Operations team can recover the system (Corrective) within the defined RTO.
If they can't, the risk is far higher than a simple CVE score suggests."

